[SkillPath "competitive_bidding/dont"]
[Student "S"]
{With 10 HCP and a solid 6-card suit this is an ideal DONT bid. You double and partner follows procedure by saying 2\C.

Now you follow procedure by showing your 6-card suit. You bid 2\H and everybody passes.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "S"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Deal "S:A2.KQ83.Q65.AJ94 T7.AJ9742.A82.KQ K5.T.KJT73.87653 QJ98643.65.94.T2"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "2S"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "S"]
1NT X pass 2S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "a14ec074824365e37e4eaca260556fd856056f558e3eff65aa980c7414133dc6"]
[Category "Competitive Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "competitive_bidding/dont"]
[Student "S"]
{Partner's double asks you to bid 2\C as a relay bid so he can name his suit.

But you don't want him to bid his 6-card suit, your hand is useless unless \Ss are trumps. So ignore the relay request and bid 2\S. Everybody passes.}

